<section id="module" class="module parallax-4">
    <h1>Cache</h1>
</section>

<div class="container project-content break">
    <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2 text-center">
        <p>Cache consignment is a platform that allows individuals to sell designer goods and receive a high value return on their items. Buyers who are interested in gently used designer items will have an opportunity to shop and purchase these items at a discounted price.</p>
        <p>While in alpha phase, Cache Consignment asked me to create a clear value proposition, gain user insight, and refine the user flow.</p>
        <%= image_tag "p1/p1-p1.png", class: "img-responsive center-block break" %>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="bg-light container">
    <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2 project-scope">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h3>PROJECT SCOPE</h3>
                <hr>
                <li>Understand main use cases</li>
                <li>Present data to be more relevant</li>
                <li>Streamline user flow</li>
                <li>Lessen the learning curve</li>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h3>DELIVERABLE</h3>
                <hr>
                <li>Presentation deck of our research and recommendations</li>
                <li>Wireframes of recommended designs</li>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h3>MY ROLE</h3>
                <hr>
                <li>User research</li>
                <li>User experience design</li>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container project-content">
    <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2 break">
        <h1>CONTEXT</h1>
        <p>Cache's founders come from the design and fashion industry. With present day fast fashion habits, Cache aims to generate awareness of the unhealthy textile ecosystem. Cache opens a second hand market for sellers to earn money and buyers to save on quality items.</p>
        <%= image_tag "p1/p1-p2.png", class: "img-responsive img-centered break" %>
        <p>Cache wanted to clarify how users will interact with the app and what features are most relevant. Were there enough userful takeaways? And, were the findings clear and actionable enough to use regularly?</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="research bg-light container project-content">

    <div class="container research project-content">
        <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
            <h1>RESEARCH</h1>
            <p>Focused efforts on understanding user behaviors, needs, and motivations through observation techniques, task analysis, and other feedback methodologies.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
            <h3>COMPETITIVE ANALYSIS</h3>
            <p>From our analysis, we learned that Cache has many well established competitors who have apps to serve their users.</p>
            <%= image_tag "p1/p1-p6.png", class: "img-responsive img-centered break" %>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
            <h3>USER INTERVIEWS</h3>
            <p>User interviews were conducted to retrieve qualitative information from potential users. The information extracted were used to construct personas and aid in design. Naturally, a few patterns emerged, and we were able to draw four provisional personas:</p>
            <div class="row border break">
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <%= image_tag "p1/p1-p10.png", class: "img-centered content-icon" %>
                    <h3>BARGAIN</h3>
                    <hr>
                    <li>Those who are looking to save a little on items that generally retail for a higher price.</li>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <%= image_tag "p1/p1-p11.png", class: "img-centered content-icon" %>
                    <h3>FASHION</h3>
                    <hr>
                    <li>Regular consumers who are looking to sell products and receive small returns.</li>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <%= image_tag "p1/p1-p12.png", class: "img-centered content-icon" %>
                    <h3>IMPULSE</h3>
                    <hr>
                    <li>Consumers who make impulsive purchases based on sale or other emotion.</li>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <%= image_tag "p1/p1-p13.png", class: "img-centered content-icon" %>
                    <h3>RESELL</h3>
                    <hr>
                    <li>Professionals who are looking to recondition used items and resell for small returns.</li>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
            <p>Users were targeted from each persona group to test our assumptions, to learn how each persona group felt toward the concept and to see how they interacted with Cache's current structure. Our interview broke down into two parts: behavioral questions and a card sort.</p>
            <blockquote class="center-block">"I like the idea of sustainable fashion but can not afford designer items."</blockquote>
            <blockquote class="center-block">"I purchased so many high end items and do not want to donate them for free."</blockquote>
            <blockquote class="center-block">"I'm always looking for great deals and sometimes buy things based on the sale"</blockquote>
            <p>Recording observations, we performed card sorting to visualize user concerns and needs.</p>
            <p class="break">Overall themes were:</p>
            <div class="row text-center break">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <%= image_tag "p1/p1-p14.png", class: "img-centered content-icon" %>
                    <li>Most time was spend on a mobile device and individuals felt comfortable with making purchases via mobile apps.</li>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <%= image_tag "p1/p1-p15.png", class: "img-centered content-icon" %>
                    <li>Most people were looking so save on items that otherwise would have costed much more.</li>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row text-center break">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <%= image_tag "p1/p1-p16.png", class: "img-centered content-icon" %>
                    <li>Rather than clothes and bags, accessories were most popular in the second hand market.</li>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <%= image_tag "p1/p1-p17.png", class: "img-centered content-icon" %>
                    <li>Sellers appreciated convenience and preferred a simple selling process.</li>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row text-center break">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <%= image_tag "p1/p1-p18.png", class: "img-centered content-icon" %>
                    <li>High end luxury items were preferred of second tierd luxury items.</li>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <%= image_tag "p1/p1-p19.png", class: "img-centered content-icon" %>
                    <li>Authentication and trust affected buyers decision making.</li>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


